ref-for-dom-usb-getdevices②.name: getDevices
ref-for-dom-usb-getdevices②.summary: The getDevices method of the USB interface returns a Promise that resolves with an array of USBDevice objects for paired attached devices. For information on pairing devices, see USB.requestDevice().
ref-for-dom-usb-getdevices②.title: USB.getDevices()

ref-for-dom-usb-onconnect.name: onconnect
ref-for-dom-usb-onconnect.summary: The onconnect property of the USB interface is an event handler called whenever a paired device is connected. It is passed an instance of USBConnectionEvent.
ref-for-dom-usb-onconnect.title: USB.onconnect

ref-for-dom-usb-ondisconnect.name: ondisconnect
ref-for-dom-usb-ondisconnect.summary: The ondisconnect property of the USB is an event handler called whenever a paired device is disconnected. It is passed an instance of USBConnectionEvent.
ref-for-dom-usb-ondisconnect.title: USB.ondisconnect

ref-for-dom-usb-requestdevice④.name: requestDevice
ref-for-dom-usb-requestdevice④.summary: The requestDevice() method of the USB interface returns a Promise that resolves with an instance of USBDevice if the specified device is found. Calling this function triggers the user agent's pairing flow.
ref-for-dom-usb-requestdevice④.title: USB.requestDevice()

usb.name: USB
usb.summary: The USB interface of the WebUSB API provides attributes and methods for finding and connecting USB devices from a web page.
usb.title: USB

usbalternateinterface.name: USBAlternateInterface
usbalternateinterface.summary: The USBAlternateInterface interface of the WebUSB API provides information about a particular configuration of an interface provided by the USB device. An interface includes one or more alternate settings which can configure a set of endpoints based on the operating mode of the device.
usbalternateinterface.title: USBAlternateInterface

dom-usbconfiguration-usbconfiguration.name: USBConfiguration
dom-usbconfiguration-usbconfiguration.summary: The USBConfiguration() constructor creates a new USBConfiguration object which contains information about the configuration on the provided USBDevice with the given configuration value.
dom-usbconfiguration-usbconfiguration.title: USBConfiguration()

ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.name: configurationName
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.summary: The configurationName read-only property of the USBConfiguration interface returns the name provided by the device to describe this configuration. This is equal to the value of the string descriptor with the index provided in the iConfiguration field of the configuration descriptor defining this configuration.
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.title: USBConfiguration.configurationName

ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.name: configurationValue
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.summary: The configurationValue read-only property of the USBConfiguration interface null
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-configurati.title: USBConfiguration.configurationValue

ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-interfaces.name: interfaces
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-interfaces.summary: The interfaces read-only property of the USBConfiguration interface returns an array containing instances of the USBInterface describing each interface supported by this configuration.
ref-for-dom-usbconfiguration-interfaces.title: USBConfiguration.interfaces

configurations.name: USBConfiguration
configurations.summary: The USBConfiguration interface of the WebUSB API provides information about a particular configuration of a USB device and the interfaces that it supports.
configurations.title: USBConfiguration

dom-usbconnectionevent-usbconnectioneven.name: USBConnectionEvent
dom-usbconnectionevent-usbconnectioneven.summary: The USBConnectionEvent() constructor creates a new USBConnectionEvent object which is passed to USB.onconnect and USB.ondisconnect. This constructor is not typically used, it is created by the browser in response to the connection and disconnection of a USB device.
dom-usbconnectionevent-usbconnectioneven.title: USBConnectionEvent()

dom-usbconnectionevent-device.name: device
dom-usbconnectionevent-device.summary: The device read-only property of the USBConnectionEvent interface returns a USBDevice object representing the device being connected or disconnected.
dom-usbconnectionevent-device.title: USBConnectionEvent.device

usbconnectionevent.name: USBConnectionEvent
usbconnectionevent.summary: The USBConnectionEvent interface of the WebUSB API is the event type passed to USB.onconnect and USB.ondisconnect when the user agent detects that a new USB device has been connected or disconnected.
usbconnectionevent.title: USBConnectionEvent

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-claiminterface②.name: claimInterface
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-claiminterface②.summary: The claimInterface() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when the requested interface is claimed for exclusive access.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-claiminterface②.title: USBDevice.claimInterface()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-clearhalt①.name: clearHalt
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-clearhalt①.summary: The clearHalt() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when a halt condition is cleared. A halt condition is when a data tranfer to or from the device has a status of 'stall', which requires the web page (the host system, in USB terminology) to clear that condition. See the for details.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-clearhalt①.title: USBDevice.clearHalt()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-close.name: close
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-close.summary: The close() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when all open interfaces are released and the device session has ended.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-close.title: USBDevice.close()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configuration①.name: configuration
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configuration①.summary: The configuration read only property of the USBDevice interface returns a USBConfiguration object for the currently selected interface for a paired USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configuration①.title: USBDevice.configuration

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configurations①.name: configurations
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configurations①.summary: The configurations read only property of the USBDevice interface an array of device-specific interfaces for controlling a paired USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-configurations①.title: USBDevice.configurations

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferin.name: controlTransferIn
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferin.summary: The controlTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBInTransferResult when the result of a command or status request has been received from the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferin.title: USBDevice.controlTransferIn()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferout.name: controlTransferOut
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferout.summary: The controlTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBOutTransferResult when a command or status operation has been transmitted to the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-controltransferout.title: USBDevice.controlTransferOut()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceclass.name: deviceClass
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceclass.summary: The deviceClass read only property of the USBDevice interface one of three properties that identify USB devices for the purpose of loading a USB driver that will work with that device. The other two properties are USBDevice.deviceSubclass and USBDevice.deviceprotocol.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceclass.title: USBDevice.deviceClass

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceprotocol.name: deviceProtocol
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceprotocol.summary: The deviceProtocol read only property of the USBDevice interface one of three properties that identify USB devices for the purpose of loading a USB driver that will work with that device. The other two properties are USBDevice.deviceClass and USBDevice.deviceSubclass.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceprotocol.title: USBDevice.deviceProtocol

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-devicesubclass.name: deviceSubclass
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-devicesubclass.summary: The deviceSubclass read only property of the USBDevice interface one of three properties that identify USB devices for the purpose of loading a USB driver that will work with that device. The other two properties are USBDevice.deviceClass and USBDevice.deviceProtocol.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-devicesubclass.title: USBDevice.deviceSubclass

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionmajor.name: deviceVersionMajor
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionmajor.summary: The deviceVersionMajor read only property of the USBDevice interface he major version number of the device in a semantic versioning scheme.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionmajor.title: USBDevice.deviceVersionMajor

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionminor.name: deviceVersionMinor
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionminor.summary: The deviceVersionMinor read only property of the USBDevice interface the minor version number of the device in a semantic versioning scheme.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionminor.title: USBDevice.deviceVersionMinor

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionsubmi.name: deviceVersionSubminor
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionsubmi.summary: The deviceVersionSubminor read only property of the USBDevice interface the patch version number of the device in a semantic versioning scheme.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-deviceversionsubmi.title: USBDevice.deviceVersionSubminor

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.name: isochronousTransferIn
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.summary: The isochronousTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBIsochronousInTransferResult when time sensitive information has been transmitted received from the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.title: USBDevice.isochronousTransferIn()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.name: isochronousTransferOut
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.summary: The isochronousTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBIsochronousOutTransferResult when time sensitive information has been transmitted to the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-isochronoustransfe.title: USBDevice.isochronousTransferOut()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-manufacturername.name: manufacturerName
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-manufacturername.summary: The manufacturerName read only property of the USBDevice interface the of the organization that manufactured the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-manufacturername.title: USBDevice.manufacturerName

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-open①.name: open
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-open①.summary: The open() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when a device session has started.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-open①.title: USBDevice.open()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-opened.name: opened
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-opened.summary: The opened read only property of the USBDevice interface indicates whether a session has been started with a paired USB device. A device must be opened before it can be controlled by a web page.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-opened.title: USBDevice.opened

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productid.name: productId
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productid.summary: The productId read only property of the USBDevice interface the manufacturer-defined code that identifies a USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productid.title: USBDevice.productId

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productname.name: productName
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productname.summary: The productName read only property of the USBDevice interface the manufacturer-defined name that identifies a USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-productname.title: USBDevice.productName

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-releaseinterface①.name: releaseInterface
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-releaseinterface①.summary: The releaseInterface() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when a cliamed interface is released from exclusive access.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-releaseinterface①.title: USBDevice.releaseInterface()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-reset.name: reset
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-reset.summary: The reset() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when the device is reset and all app operations canceled and their promises rejected.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-reset.title: USBDevice.reset()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectalternateint.name: selectAlternateInterface
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectalternateint.summary: The selectAlternateInterface() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when the specified alternative endpoint is selected.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectalternateint.title: USBDevice.selectAlternateInterface()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectconfiguratio.name: selectConfiguration
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectconfiguratio.summary: The selectConfiguration() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves when the specified configuration is selected.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-selectconfiguratio.title: USBDevice.selectConfiguration()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-serialnumber.name: serialNumber
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-serialnumber.summary: The serialNumber read only property of the USBDevice interface is the manufacturer-defined serial number for the specific USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-serialnumber.title: USBDevice.serialNumber

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferin①.name: transferIn
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferin①.summary: The transferIn() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBTransferInResult when bulk or interrupt data is received from the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferin①.title: USBDevice.transferIn()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferout.name: transferOut
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferout.summary: The transferOut() method of the USBDevice interface returns a promise that resolves with a USBTransferOutResult when bulk or interrupt data is sent to the USB device.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-transferout.title: USBDevice.transferOut()

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionmajor.name: usbVersionMajor
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionmajor.summary: The usbVersionMajor read only property of the USBDevice interface is one of three properties that declare the USB protocol version supported by the device. The other two properties are USBDevice.usbVersionMinor and USBDevice.usbVersionSubminor.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionmajor.title: USBDevice.usbVersionMajor

dom-usbdevice-usbversionminor.name: usbVersionMinor
dom-usbdevice-usbversionminor.summary: The usbVersionMinor read only property of the USBDevice interface is one of three properties that declare the USB protocol version supported by the device. The other two properties are USBDevice.usbVersionMajor and USBDevice.usbVersionSubminor.
dom-usbdevice-usbversionminor.title: USBDevice.usbVersionMinor

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionsubminor.name: usbVersionSubminor
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionsubminor.summary: The usbVersionSubminor read only property of the USBDevice interface is one of three properties that declare the USB protocol version supported by the device. The other two properties are USBDevice.usbVersionMajor and USBDevice.usbVersionMinor.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-usbversionsubminor.title: USBDevice.usbVersionSubminor

ref-for-dom-usbdevice-vendorid.name: vendorId
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-vendorid.summary: The vendorId read only property of the USBDevice interface is the official usg.org-assigned vendor ID.
ref-for-dom-usbdevice-vendorid.title: USBDevice.vendorId

device-usage.name: USBDevice
device-usage.summary: The USBDevice interface of the WebUSB API provides access to metadata about a paired USB device and methods for controlling it.
device-usage.title: USBDevice

endpoints.name: USBEndpoint
endpoints.summary: The USBEndpoint interface of the WebUSB API provides information about an endpoint provided by the USB device. An endpoint represents a unidirectional data stream into or out of a device.
endpoints.title: USBEndpoint

usbintransferresult.name: USBInTransferResult
usbintransferresult.summary: The USBInTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the transferIn() and controlTransferIn() methods of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB device to the USB host.
usbintransferresult.title: USBInTransferResult

usbinterface.name: USBInterface
usbinterface.summary: The USBInterface interface of the WebUSB API provides information about an interface provided by the USB device. An interface represents a feature of the device which implements a particular protocol and may contain endpoints for bidirectional communication.
usbinterface.title: USBInterface

usbisochronousintransferpacket.name: USBIsochronousInTransferPacket
usbisochronousintransferpacket.summary: The USBIsochronousInTransferPacket interface of the WebUSB API is part of the response from a call to the isochronousTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the status of an individual packet from a request to transfer data from the USB device to the USB host over an isochronous endpoint.
usbisochronousintransferpacket.title: USBIsochronousInTransferPacket

usbisochronousintransferresult.name: USBIsochronousInTransferResult
usbisochronousintransferresult.summary: The USBIsochronousInTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the isochronousTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB device to the USB host.
usbisochronousintransferresult.title: USBIsochronousInTransferResult

usbisochronousouttransferpacket.name: USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket
usbisochronousouttransferpacket.summary: The USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket interface of the WebUSB API is part of the response from a call to the isochronousTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the status of an individual packet from a request to transfer data from the USB host to the USB device over an isochronous endpoint.
usbisochronousouttransferpacket.title: USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket

usbisochronousouttransferresult.name: USBIsochronousOutTransferResult
usbisochronousouttransferresult.summary: The USBIsochronousOutTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the isochronousTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB host to the USB device.
usbisochronousouttransferresult.title: USBIsochronousOutTransferResult

usbouttransferresult.name: USBOutTransferResult
usbouttransferresult.summary: The USBOutTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the transferOut() and controlTransferOut() methods of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB host to the USB device.
usbouttransferresult.title: USBOutTransferResult

permissions-policy.name: usb
permissions-policy.summary: The HTTP Feature-Policy header usb directive controls whether the current document is allowed to use the WebUSB API.
permissions-policy.title: Feature-Policy: usb
